      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GREY CADILLAC (1) is in a purple patch of form having come from wider barriers to win his last two outings, the latest at this circuit and distance when getting home by 1.2 metres after working to the front. Looks suited by the ace draw so is capable of getting the job done again. MISTER JONES NZ (3) has been going well at Menangle of late, finishing runner-up two back before drawing deep and racing parked when midfield last week. Major player in this suitable assignment. ROCKY MONALOO (9) was well supported when resuming for the new yard and led but faded to fifth. Fitter so may be worth another chance. RAINBOW TITAN (8) was runner-up from this barrier last week, giving him two wins and two placings from his last four starts. Respect.",
